> --- In junit@yahoogroups.com, "Kyle Gabhart <kylegabhart@y...>"
> <kylegabhart@y...> wrote:
>
> I love JUnit.  It's a great testing framework.  What is the deal
> though with the frog and the slogan - "keep the bar green to keep the
> code clean..."?

As people have explained, you should get the slogan now.  But personally, I
used to wonder about the frog too.  IMO, the staring, blinking frog graphic
is extremely cheesy.  He's got no personality and is not even clothed, like
a good civilized frog (a la Michigan J. Frog,
http://www.who2.com/michiganjfrog.html).

Maybe we should have a contest to come up with a better frog, or have a vote
to do away with the frog and come up with a cool logo for JUnit, like they
do for a lot of the Jakarta projects.

Scott Stirling
